'''Dathomir Magic''' was the general name given to the use of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and [[Force power/Legends|Force powers]] by the [[Witches of Dathomir]].

Originally, the rogue [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Allya/Legends|Allya]], who was [[Exile (punishment)/Legends|exiled]] to [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]], taught the powers of the Force to her children there, giving them an evolutionary advantage over the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] other inhabitants. After [[Gethzerion]] founded the [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsisters]], she developed her own brand of [[Magic/Legends|magic]] that her coven coined '''Shadow Magic''', or more colloquially as '''magicks'''. As a result, the other witch clans took to calling their own practices '''Allyan Magic''', believing that the Nightsisters had corrupted the beauty of Allya's original magic.

==Description==
There were two schools of Dathomir Magic. The first, traditional Allyan Magic, followed rules put forth in the [[Book of Law/Legends|Book of Law]], a tome of [[Light side of the Force/Legends|moral and ethical teachings]] kept and modified by each clan based on an original created by [[Allya/Legends|Allya]] for her daughters. The [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|other]], called "Shadow Magic" by its originator, [[Gethzerion]], was the provenance of the [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsisters]] that did not require chanting or other primitive rituals. The Nightsisters' book, the [[Book of Shadows]], told of future glories that they would gather in the heavens.

The practitioners of Dathomir Magic believed themselves to be casting spells rather than making use of the Force, and often were unable to make use of a "spell" without speaking its assigned name or performing the ritualized singing, dancing, chanting, and/or writing associated with it. The Nightsisters often attributed the work of the Force to the [[Spirit (Nightsisters)|Spirits]] instead.

The skills in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] that the [[Witches of Dathomir]] possessed changed the many generations since Allya's arrival on [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]], as knowledge was shaped by traditions and time from what Allya originally taught. It seemed that the Witches were only gifted in certain aspects of using the Force, some in [[Force healing/Legends|healing]], others in [[Telekinesis/Legends#Force Whirlwind|Force Whirlwind]], and so forth.

According to the Nightsisters, a [[Shaman of the Nightsisters|shaman]] could channel the [[Spirit (Nightsisters)|Spirits]] to create green [[Spirit ichor/Legends|spirit ichor]], which&mdash;by the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]&mdash;served as the primary basis of their magicks. The [[Water of Life/Legends|Water of Life]] was one such use of spirit ichor.

==History==
During the Clone Wars, [[Mother (title)/Legends|Mother]] [[Talzin/Legends|Talzin]] and her Nightsister clan had used their magick to enhance [[Savage Opress/Legends|Savage Opress's]] features: longer horns, taller, and larger physique, turning him into an avatar of primal anger. Talzin later used her magick to cure [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]] of his insanity and grant him [[Cybernetics/Legends|prosthetic]] legs.

